This paper focuses on developing data-driven approaches to improve the semi-autonomous telemanipulation of robot hands, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to learn preferred assistance strategies, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of vision-based sensing for object manipulation, which could relate to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper emphasizes the importance of accommodating human inputs and making the system intuitive for the operator, which suggests a connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
